---
// A printable, shareable checklist for the writers' room. Static markup, no JS.
---
<div class="panel p-6 md:p-10 print:bg-white print:text-black">
  <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-gold-400">Writers' Room Checklist</p>
  <h3 class="mt-1 font-display text-2xl text-white">
    10 questions to ask your script before greenlight.
  </h3>
  <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-white/60 max-w-2xl">
    Print it. Run a scene through it. None of these are wrong answers — they're
    just questions worth asking out loud in the room.
  </p>

  <ol class="mt-8 grid gap-3 md:grid-cols-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">01.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Who in the scene is feeling shame, and what specifically triggered it?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">02.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Who in the scene is feeling pride — for whose accomplishment?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">03.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">If you flipped the genders of the people involved, would the scene still play?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">04.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Is the shame self-administered, or is it being delivered by another character?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">05.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Does anyone in the scene get to <em>refuse</em> the shame? On what grounds?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">06.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">If pride is being celebrated, is it for who someone <em>is</em> or what they <em>did</em>?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">07.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Whose voice is missing from the scene that the consequence falls on?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">08.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Have we seen this exact framing 100 times? 1,000 times? Is that intentional?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">09.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">If a 14-year-old in the audience watched only this scene, what would they learn was normal?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">10.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">What's one line you could change to make the underlying assumption visible to the audience?</span>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 text-xs text-white/40">
    <button onclick="window.print()" class="rounded-full bg-white/5 px-4 py-2 text-white/70 ring-1 ring-white/10 hover:bg-white/10 hover:text-white transition print:hidden">
      Print this checklist
    </button>
    <span>or screenshot — it's CC-BY.</span>
  </div>
</div>
